Top BTech Colleges in India Based on 2024 Ranking

Sushil Pandey

Senior Content Specialist | Updated on - Feb 19, 2024

Latest Notifications

  • 22 February, 2024 : PM Modi Inaugurated Two Complexes at IIT Delhi on February 21; Read More Here
  • 18 February, 2024 : IIT Madras Launches AI-Powered English Learning Platform for Students

India has a total of 4,658 engineering colleges offering Bachelor of Technology (BTech) courses in various disciplines. Out of these colleges, there are 4,151 top BTech colleges in India including the government and public colleges. The number of students applying for the course has increased significantly in recent years as the scope of BTech is extremely wide, which has led to the division of the course into many specializations. 

  • IIT Madras is the best BTech college in India. It is ranked 1 followed by IIT New Delhi and IIT Bombay among the top Engineering colleges in India.
  • Some of the most popular BTech branches include Civil Engineering, Computer Science Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, Electronics & Communication Engineering, and Chemical Engineering among many others. 
  • At present, there are a total of 23 IITs spread all over the country. The list of some of the top colleges in India includes IIT Madras, IIT Bombay, IIT Delhi, IIT Kharagpur, IIT Kanpur, etc.
  • After IITs, NITs (National Institute of Technology) are the ones considered after IITs by most of the BTech aspirants. There is a total of 31 NITs spread across the country. The list of some of the topmost NITs includes the NIT Tiruchirapalli, NIT Warangal, NIT Karnataka, NIT Hamirpur, etc.
  • Indian Institute of Technology (IIT), Madras has been ranked as the best BTech college in India by NIRF followed by IIT Delhi and IIT Bombay.

Top BTech Colleges in India: Ranking

There are several ranking agencies and top magazines that rank various institutions across the country based on several parameters. The strategy followed differs from agency to agency. However, some of the common parameters include teacher-student ratio, placements, faculty quality, infrastructure, and more. The Economics Times, QS rankings, India Today, Outlook, The Week, and NIRF are some of the most reputed ranking agencies in India. These ranking agencies rank different institutions in different categories. Given below are the top BTech colleges in India with ranking.

Top BTech Colleges in India with NIRF Ranking 2023

The National Institutional Ranking Framework is a method that the Indian government adopts to rank top Education institutions in India based on various parameters. It is under the Ministry of Education. Every year NIRF publishes ranking lists of top Institutions in India for different domains. NIRF is the most trustworthy and popular Ranking agency in India.

NIRF ranks the institutions across India based on 5 parameters and they are (1) Teaching, Learning & Resources, (2) Research and Professional Practice, (3) Graduation Outcomes, (4) Outreach and Inclusivity, and, (5) Perception. The rendered pie chart below depicts the weightage of different parameters used for Ranking top colleges in India:

Source: NIRF Official Website

  • IIT Madras is the best BTech college in India, per NIRF Ranking 2023. It is ranked at 1 with an 89.89 NIRF score. 
  • The rankings of IIT Delhi, IIT Bombay, and IIT Kanpur remain unchanged. However, IIT Roorkee has shown improvement and it has overtaken IIT Kharagpur. 
  • IIT Guwahati has maintained its position at 7th. It is followed by IIT Hyderabad which has overtaken IIT Tiruchirappalli and has achieved +1.

  • IIT Varanasi has seen a fall in its ranking this year. It has dropped to 15 from 13. It is followed by NIT Rourkela and IIT ISM Dhanbad at 16th and 17th place.

Top BTech Colleges in India: Return on Investment (ROI)

Return On Investment (ROI) value plays a vital role when it comes to choosing the top BTech college. BTech is a very expensive course that can cost a fat sum of money which in turn can be an unnecessary burden on the student and the parents. Investing in one of the top government BTech colleges assures one of a bright future. But when it comes to private colleges then one has to take into account several parameters to shortlist any college. One important parameter is the fee charged by the college.

The ROI values for some of the top BTech colleges in India are listed below:

  • Jadavpur University is ranked 1st among the above best BTech colleges in India in terms of ROI. The University offers the highest ROI percentage.
  • Jamia Millia Islamia stands in the 2nd position followed by DTU Delhi at 3rd among the top BTech colleges in India with high ROI.
  • BITS Pilani is one of the Top Private BTech Colleges in India. It offers 6 times ROI when compared to its average annual fees. 
  • VIT Vellore and ICT Mumbai are some other top BTech colleges in India that promise a high return on investment.
College/ University Name  Average Annual Fees  Annual Placement Package ROI* Rank

Top BTech Colleges in India: Admission Process

India has a total of 4,151 BTech colleges, out of which 594 are public and 3548 are private. These colleges offer high-quality professional technical education both full-time and part-time. The following chart shows the total number of private and public BTech colleges in India.

  • Lakhs of aspirants apply for the BTech program every year. Most of the top BTech collin edges in India rely on the scores of various national-level entrance exams to shortlist students for admission into the BTech program. 
  • JEE Mains, JEE Advanced, UPSEE, BITand SAT, and VITEEE are some of the popular entrance exams among all the other exams.

Indian Institute of Technology (IIT), Delhi

IIT Delhi is one of the best engineering colleges in India. It was established in the year 1961 and has been declared an Institute of national importance. It was also internationally ranked number 3 in the QS World University Rankings.    

  • The graduate programs offered by IIT Delhi include B. Tech, a Dual Degree program, and an Integrated M. Tech program. The college also offers masters-level programs like M.Tech, Ph. D, MBA, M.Des, PG Diploma, etc.
  • The specializations in engineering offered by IIT Delhi are Biochemical Engineering and Biotechnology, Chemical Engineering, Computer Science and Engineering, Civil Engineering, Electrical Engineering, Mathematics, Physics, Textile Technology, and Mechanical Engineering.
  • IIT Delhi accepts students with very high ranks through selection exams like JEE (BTech) and GATE (MTech).
  • The average annual fee for the B.Tech program is INR 2,36,600 and for the M.Tech program is INR 51,100.

IIT Delhi Placement Highlights

IIT Delhi conducted its placement drive for batch 2022. There has been an increase of 45% in the number of offers received.

  • There were 1250 job offers made which included 350 International offers and 180 Pre-Placement offers made by over 350 participating recruiters. Tech giant Microsoft made more than 60 offers.
  • More than 500+ job profiles across multiple domains were offered by 300+ national and international recruiters. 
  • The students bagged over 925 job offers in the first phase of placements surpassing the institute’s expectations. More than 200 firms have hired students for around 250 different job profiles, including pre-placement offers. 
  • Around 90% of students have bagged offers in their core areas. Over 20 International selections have been made by countries whereas offers have been received from several countries such as Japan, the Middle East, Singapore, South Korea, and Taiwan.
  • 13 students have opted for the deferred placements facility. Students opting for this option can avail of the placement services once for up to 2 years.
  • Some of the top recruiters on the campus in terms of the maximum number of recruitments include Microsoft, Intel, Oracle, Tata Projects, EXL Services, ICICI Bank, Goldman Sachs, HCL, Wells Fargo, and IQVIA.

It is one of the most prestigious and best engineering colleges in the country with a NIRF ranking of 1. It was established in 2008.

  • IIT Madras has 16 academic departments and numerous research centers that offer postgraduate and undergraduate programs in distinct disciplines of Engineering, Technology, and Pure Sciences.

  • Students who are willing to get admitted here must give the national entrance exam of JEE in advance for B.Tech and GATE for M.Tech.
  • IIT Madras is offering a scholarship for B.Sc in Programming and Data Science students having an annual family income of INR 1 Lakh. The students will get financial aid for 4 academic semesters.

Vellore Institute of Technology (VIT), Chennai

The institute has two campuses one in Vellore and the other one in Chennai. VIT Chennai campus is spread across 360 acres of land and the Chennai campus is spread over 150 acres of land.

Top BTech Colleges in India: Entrance Exam Wise

The students who prefer to pursue their careers in the top BTech college in India can apply through the national-level entrance exams. The most popular entrance exam for BTech aspirants in India is JEE. JEE score not only leads to the topmost BTech colleges in India, but it also forms the first step for entering into the portals of the most prestigious IITs.

  • Some of the top private universities rely on the score of self-conducted entrance tests. Some of the most popular entrance exams conducted by private universities include BITSAT, VITEEE, SRMJEEE, etc. 
  • All the IITs rely on the score of JEE Advanced for shortlisting candidates for admission.

Top BTech Colleges in India Through JEE Main

JEE is an acronym for the Joint Entrance Exam. All the IITs rely on the JEE Advanced score for admission while most of the other colleges rely on the JEE Main score for shortlisting candidates for admission. The exam is divided into two parts, Mains and Advanced. First, the candidate is required to appear for the Main exam. The students who qualify for the Mains become eligible for taking the JEE Advanced test.

Some of the top BTech colleges in India accepting JEE Main scores are given below:

  • National Institute of Technology (NIT), Jamshedpur
  • National Institute of Technology (NIT), Warangal
  • National Institute of Technology (NIT), Tiruchirappalli
  • National Institute of Technology (NIT), Karnataka
  • Amity University, Noida
  • Punjab engineering college, Chandigarh
  • Jamia Millia Islamia, New Delhi
  • Thapar Institute of engineering and technology, Patiala

Top BTech Colleges in India Through UPSEE

Uttar Pradesh State Entrance Exam (UPSEE) is a state-level entrance exam conducted by universities in Uttar Pradesh. Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam Technical University (AKTU), UP is the conducting body for the exam. It is widely accepted by many top BTech colleges in India to shortlist candidates for admission. 

Some of the top BTech colleges in India accepting UPSEE test scores are given below: 

  • Ajay Kumar Garg engineering college, Ghaziabad
  • Institute of engineering and technology, Lucknow
  • GL Bajaj institute of technology and management, Greater Noida
  • Galgotias college of engineering and technology greater Noida
  • ABES engineering college, Ghaziabad

Top BTech Colleges in India: FAQs

Ques: How many IITs are there in India?

Ans: There is a total of 23 IITs spread across the country.

Ques: How many NITs are there in India?

Ans: There is a total of 31 NITs spread across the country.

Ques: How can I get admissiotoin National Institute of Technology (NIT), Tiruchirappalli?

Ans: National Institute of Technology (NIT), Trichy accepts the JEE Mains score for shortlisting candidates for admission. It is the topmost NIT in India to fetch a BTech seat in NIT, Trichy one must score extremely well in JEE Mains.

Ques: What are the BTech fees in private colleges?

Ans: The cost of pursuing BTech in India varies from INR 1 lakh to 20 lakhs.

Ques: Which is the best private college for pursuing ing BTech?

Ans: Some of the top private BTech colleges in India are Birla Institute of Technology and Science (BITS), Pilani, Vellore Institute of Technology (VIT), Chennai, and SRM Chennai among many others.

Ques: What are the various BTech branches one can choose from?

Ans: Various BTech branches include civil engineering, computer science engineering, mechanical engineering, automobile engineering, electrical engineering, chemical engineering, and mining engineering among many others.

Ques: Which BTech specialization fetches the highest salary packages?

Ans: As per the recent trends, computer science engineering fetches the highest salary packages.

Ques: Which IIT has been ranked as the best among all the other IITs by NIRF?
